						<font size="8"/>
					</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[NOTE : The bill for withdrawal of advances / final withdrawal should be supported by a duly certified copy of the sanction in the proper from the letter of authority issued by the Audit Office. In the case of non-gazetted Government servants. the copy should be attested by the Head of the Office. In the case of bill for withdrawal of payment of insurance premia reference to the letter of authority issued by the Audit officer permitting the withdrawal should be quoted as also reference to this stock number allotted in the policy assigned in favour of the Government of Tamil Nadu and sent to the Audit Officer for safe custody. Certified 5 (a) or (b) may be retained according as the number of policies do not exceed or exceed four  in each individual case. The drawing officers should not present and Treasury officers should not honour the bills in the respect of claims made after the expiry of the period of grace allowed from the due date for the payment of premium specified in the statement below the certifiede (2). The period of grace should invariably be mentioned in the bill.]]></text>
